---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";import Breadcrumbs from "../components/content/Breadcrumbs.astro";import dataset from "../data/sizing/goalie-leg-pads-us-v0.1.json";import manifest from "../data/sizing/manifest.json";
const breadcrumbs=[{label:"Home",href:"/"},{label:"Methodology"}];
---
<BaseLayout title="Sizing methodology and data provenance | Goalie Gear Fit" description="How Goalie Gear Fit sources, reviews, tests and publishes goalie-pad sizing rules." canonicalPath="/methodology" {breadcrumbs}><Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs}/><article class="content"><h1>Sizing methodology and provenance</h1><p>This site consumes only reviewed, schema-validated published data. Runtime pages do not read raw manufacturer snapshots or invent missing sizing rules.</p><section class="card"><h2>Published dataset</h2><dl><dt>Dataset</dt><dd>{dataset.datasetId}</dd><dt>Version</dt><dd>{dataset.version}</dd><dt>Market</dt><dd>{dataset.market}</dd><dt>Reviewed</dt><dd>{dataset.reviewedAt}</dd><dt>Rules</dt><dd>{dataset.rules.length}</dd></dl></section><section class="card"><h2>Evidence pipeline</h2><p>Source evidence moves through raw registration, normalization, editorial draft review and schema-validated publication. The site vendors only the published dataset, schema, manifest and executable fixtures.</p><ul>{Object.entries(manifest.files).map(([name,value])=><li><code>{name}</code>: <code>{typeof value==="string"?value:JSON.stringify(value)}</code></li>)}</ul></section><section class="card"><h2>How recommendations are checked</h2><p>The deterministic engine reads rule dimensions and brand-support metadata at call time. Published fixtures cover boundaries, overlaps, gaps, conflicts, extensions and unsupported Vaughn inputs. CI verifies sha256 hashes, JSON Schema, all fixtures, the static build and the output allowlist before a commit can proceed.</p></section><section class="card"><h2>Fail-closed policy</h2><p>No official mapping, missing required measurements, source gaps and conflicting methods return cannot determine or conflict. The tool never selects the nearest size to fill absent evidence.</p></section><p>{dataset.safetyDisclaimer}</p></article></BaseLayout>
